Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	figure legend:Suppl. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. NF-kappa-B via RICK (CARDIAK, RIP2) and IKK-gamma. Confers responsiveness to intracellular bacterial lipopolysaccharides (LPS)"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of Blau syndrome (BS) [MIM:186580]. BS is a rare autosomal dominant disorder characterized by early-onset granulomatous arthritis, uveitis and skin rash"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to Crohn disease (CD) [MIM:266600]. CD is a form of remitting inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). CD may involve any part of the gastrointestinal tract, but most frequently the terminal ileum and colon. Bowel inflammation is transmural and discontinuous. Crohn disease is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to ulcerative colitis [MIM:191390]. It is a chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In ulcerative colitis, the inflammation is continuous and limited to rectal and colonic mucosal layers. Ulcerative colitis is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS) [MIM:609464]. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:1B|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:4932(yeasx)|taxid:4932("Saccharomyces cerevisiae (Baker's yeast)")	-	2015/07/07	2025/07/31	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:GhAhVuXMNxi6P5J0CfNi5l9bjRk9606	intact-crc:CB5391C752F70646|rigid:8GNKswWWokd1AtXj5Pzyy7mwoiE	false	mutation decreasing interaction strength:702-702	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0396"(predetermined participant)	psi-mi:"MI:0396"(predetermined participant)

Confers responsiveness to intracellular bacterial lipopolysaccharides (LPS)"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of Blau syndrome (BS) [MIM:186580]. BS is a rare autosomal dominant disorder characterized by early-onset granulomatous arthritis, uveitis and skin rash"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to Crohn disease (CD) [MIM:266600]. CD is a form of remitting inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). CD may involve any part of the gastrointestinal tract, but most frequently the terminal ileum and colon. Bowel inflammation is transmural and discontinuous. Crohn disease is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to ulcerative colitis [MIM:191390]. It is a chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In ulcerative colitis, the inflammation is continuous and limited to rectal and colonic mucosal layers. Ulcerative colitis is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS) [MIM:609464]. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:1C|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:9606(human-sw480)|taxid:9606(Homo sapiens SW480 adenocarcinoma cell)	-	2015/07/07	2025/07/31	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:GhAhVuXMNxi6P5J0CfNi5l9bjRk9606	intact-crc:5A98A8B462D5604B|rigid:8GNKswWWokd1AtXj5Pzyy7mwoiE	false	ha tag:?-?	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0113"(western blot)	psi-mi:"MI:0113"(western blot)

CD is a form of remitting inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). CD may involve any part of the gastrointestinal tract, but most frequently the terminal ileum and colon. In ulcerative colitis, the inflammation is continuous and limited to rectal and colonic mucosal layers. Ulcerative colitis is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS) [MIM:609464]. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:1D|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:9606(human-sw480)|taxid:9606(Homo sapiens SW480 adenocarcinoma cell)	-	2015/07/07	2025/07/31	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:GhAhVuXMNxi6P5J0CfNi5l9bjRk9606	intact-crc:7CF23C23872F8E44|rigid:8GNKswWWokd1AtXj5Pzyy7mwoiE	false	ha tag:?-?	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)

Ulcerative colitis is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS) [MIM:609464]. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:2 B/C, 4D, Supp fig 1.|comment:The NOD2-R702W  mutant showed decreased binding and the L1007fs variant, which is an insertion/frameshift mutant  truncated at amino acid 1007, did not bind to Vimentin.|antagonist:"Withaferin A (WFA, CHEBI:69120 ), a steroidal lactone from the plant Withania somnifera and a Vimentin inhibitor."|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:9606(human-293)|taxid:9606(Homo sapiens HEK293 embryonic kidney cell)	-	2015/07/07	2025/07/31	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:GhAhVuXMNxi6P5J0CfNi5l9bjRk9606	intact-crc:8F7A9E1809216828|rigid:8GNKswWWokd1AtXj5Pzyy7mwoiE	false	necessary binding region:1008-1040|ha tag:?-?|mutation decreasing interaction strength:702-702	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)

membrane)	comment:mint|comment:homomint|function:"Induces NF-kappa-B via RICK (CARDIAK, RIP2) and IKK-gamma. Confers responsiveness to intracellular bacterial lipopolysaccharides (LPS)"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of Blau syndrome (BS) [MIM:186580]. BS is a rare autosomal dominant disorder characterized by early-onset granulomatous arthritis, uveitis and skin rash"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to Crohn disease (CD) [MIM:266600]. CD is a form of remitting inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). CD may involve any part of the gastrointestinal tract, but most frequently the terminal ileum and colon. Bowel inflammation is transmural and discontinuous. Crohn disease is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to ulcerative colitis [MIM:191390]. It is a chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In ulcerative colitis, the inflammation is continuous and limited to rectal and colonic mucosal layers. Ulcerative colitis is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS) [MIM:609464]. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:3E|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:9606(human-293)|taxid:9606(Homo sapiens HEK293 embryonic kidney cell)	-	2015/07/07	2025/07/31	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:GhAhVuXMNxi6P5J0CfNi5l9bjRk9606	intact-crc:9F84BE45844B2E18|rigid:8GNKswWWokd1AtXj5Pzyy7mwoiE	false	-	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:1200"(immunocytochemistry)	psi-mi:"MI:1200"(immunocytochemistry)

Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:no figure-3|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:4932(yeasx)|taxid:4932("Saccharomyces cerevisiae (Baker's yeast)")	-	2015/07/07	2025/06/23	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:mOWun+rOiFbfy4AZ1pQ+K3GRriU9606	intact-crc:13F7AA5F0CE08256|rigid:kbkAs5uynixHJohHLF8s1vTgBEw	false	-	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0078"(nucleotide sequence identification)	psi-mi:"MI:0078"(nucleotide sequence identification)

NF-kappa-B via RICK (CARDIAK, RIP2) and IKK-gamma. Confers responsiveness to intracellular bacterial lipopolysaccharides (LPS)"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of Blau syndrome (BS) [MIM:186580]. BS is a rare autosomal dominant disorder characterized by early-onset granulomatous arthritis, uveitis and skin rash"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to Crohn disease (CD) [MIM:266600]. CD is a form of remitting inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). CD may involve any part of the gastrointestinal tract, but most frequently the terminal ileum and colon. Bowel inflammation is transmural and discontinuous. Crohn disease is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to ulcerative colitis [MIM:191390]. It is a chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In ulcerative colitis, the inflammation is continuous and limited to rectal and colonic mucosal layers. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:no figure-5|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:9606(human-sw480)|taxid:9606(Homo sapiens SW480 adenocarcinoma cell)	-	2015/07/07	2025/01/20	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:JvtMfge2Q7fuGOTLSWqR3syL/3s9606	intact-crc:CD218FF8C4847CEB|rigid:S6EA3eMjTZNsoiLJvPvjcOwAlJw	false	myc tag:n-n	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)

BS is a rare autosomal dominant disorder characterized by early-onset granulomatous arthritis, uveitis and skin rash"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to Crohn disease (CD) [MIM:266600]. CD is a form of remitting inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). CD may involve any part of the gastrointestinal tract, but most frequently the terminal ileum and colon. Bowel inflammation is transmural and discontinuous. Crohn disease is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are a cause of susceptibility to ulcerative colitis [MIM:191390]. It is a chronic inflammatory bowel disease. In ulcerative colitis, the inflammation is continuous and limited to rectal and colonic mucosal layers. Ulcerative colitis is commonly classified as autoimmune disease"|function:"Defects in NOD2 are the cause of early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS) [MIM:609464]. Sarcoidosis is a multiorganic inflammatory disease with unknown etiology, characterized by the histologic features of non-caseating epithelioid granulomas. In childhood, 2 distinct types of sarcoidosis have been described. Usually the disease is detected in older children by chest radiography and the clinical manifestations are characterized by a classical triad of lung, lymph node, and eye involvement, similar to those in adults. In contrast, early-onset sarcoidosis (EOS), which usually appears in those younger than 4 years of age, is quite rare and has a distinct triad of skin, joint, and eye disorders, without apparent pulmonary involvement. Compared with an asymptomatic and sometimes naturally disappearing course of the disease in older children, EOS is progressive and in many cases causes severe complications, such as blindness, joint destruction, and visceral involvement"	-	figure legend:Fig 1|curation depth:imex curation|dataset:IBD - Inflammatory bowel disease|dataset:Crohn's disease - Interactions of proteins identified as having a link to Crohn's disease|full coverage:Only protein-protein interactions	taxid:9606(human-sw480)|taxid:9606(Homo sapiens SW480 adenocarcinoma cell)	-	2015/07/07	2025/07/31	rogid:cEF3hnDQW90TWXNDH/uqW6/wMhI9606	rogid:GhAhVuXMNxi6P5J0CfNi5l9bjRk9606	intact-crc:C215BC1A4E8D74DC|rigid:8GNKswWWokd1AtXj5Pzyy7mwoiE	false	myc tag:n-n	-	-	-	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)	psi-mi:"MI:0705"(anti tag western blot)
